Make a MERN stack banking application. The MERN stack consists of:

MongoDB — document database (backend)
Express(.js) — Node.js server-side web framework (Middle Tier)
React(.js) — a client-side JavaScript framework (front end)
Node(.js) — the premier JavaScript web server platform (Middle Tier)


This banking application has the ability to create an account, login with email and password or google account (and logout) via firebase authentication, withdraw, deposit, see balance.

1. Download the files or clone this repository 

2. In the public folder in the context.js file, update the firebaseConfig with your own account info:
var firebaseConfig = {
  apiKey: "",
  authDomain: "",
  databaseURL: "",
  projectId: "",
  storageBucket: "",
  messagingSenderId: "",
  appId: ""
};

3. Open the root directory in VS code
4. Right click on the Dockerfile and select "build image"
5. Open the VS code terminal and run:
	docker run -dp 3000:3000 badbankluers  

